All parameter DocIDs in Maestro must be mapped to the Map Table below. In Maestro, when a user mouses over a parameter a link appears. 
If the link is clicked, Maestro opens a browser at the Online Help for that parameter.

User mouses over a parameter which has:
DocID = 1046 (DocID is common to Maestro and Online Help)

base_url=<root-path-to-folder>/Responsive HTML5/Ncore3_Online_Documentation/User_Guide/Parameters/Parameters.htm#CSH_
CSH_number = 94 (map number to construct url)
full_url = base_url + CSH_number = <root-path-to-folder>/Responsive HTML5/Ncore3_Online_Documentation/User_Guide/Parameters/Parameters.htm#CSH_94

On click, browser opens full_url showing Online Help for that parameter.
